The paper deals with the problem of distributed coordination between autonomous robots, which is a classic problem in distributed computing (cs.DC). The problem specifically involves mobile robots, which suggests the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes an algorithm to solve the problem, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithm is designed to work in a semi-synchronous model, which involves the study of synchronization in distributed systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of fault tolerance, which is a common concern in multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
